-- Elisbaeth Murdoch to step down as Shine Group chairman -FT
-- 
-- Tue Sep 30, 2014 07:51PM EDT
-- None



Sept 30 (Reuters) - Elisabeth Murdoch, the daughter of media mogul Rupert Murdoch, will step down as the chairman of Shine Group when it merges with Endemol and Core Media Group Inc[CKXETM.UL], the Financial Times reported, citing people familiar with the matter.

Twenty-First Century Fox Inc<FOXA.O> said in May that it would form a joint venture with Endemol, Shine Group and Core Media Group.[ID:nBw9PwbFLa] Sophie Turner Laing, the former managing director of content at British Sky Broadcasting Group Plc<BSY.L>, has been named chief executive of the merged entity, the Financial Times reported.  <^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^The read the Financial Times article click here: http://on.ft.com/1owoY48 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^>  Elisabeth, founded and sold her Shine Group television business to News Corp<NWSA.O> in 2011.[ID:nL4N0MN27S] She was set to obtain a seat on the board of directors at News Corp, but decided against pursuing the nomination following the phone hacking scandal that dogged the company.